{"id": "1423663125617578145", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "693983290423509042", "author_name": "climbkaly", "content": "Lily, Castor and Ogier are the main shielders for ultra.\n\nYou can also use Clem (not for sheild, but heal). Once you rouse Clem, if you play her healing card first it activates twice.", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T13:28:59.529000+00:00", "type": 19, "edited_timestamp": "2025-10-03T13:31:07.409000+00:00", "mentions": ["299711905751105536"], "reply_to": "1423649631061016798"}
{"id": "1423664068937388214", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "693983290423509042", "author_name": "climbkaly", "content": "Take out Ryker, put in Horla.\n\nPut horla into sad for Salv.", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T13:32:44.434000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["301852497360846849"], "reply_to": "1423568012107059230"}
{"id": "1423683802622066759", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "299711905751105536", "author_name": "pickles4701", "content": "Currently using Clem and Ogier. I guess I'll just stick with it and see how far I get", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T14:51:09.311000+00:00"}
{"id": "1423686039267971153", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "299711905751105536", "author_name": "pickles4701", "content": "My main issue with Ultra is that leap effect just conflicts with itself. Seems like using more than two ultra units is just inefficient", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T15:00:02.569000+00:00"}
{"id": "1423687880894582814", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "693983290423509042", "author_name": "climbkaly", "content": "You get used to it and learn which leap effects are better than others.\n\nAlso all leap happens in ultra space. Quasar just lowers the cost of each card.\n\nWanting certain cards to be played in ultra space can take a priority over what the leap effect does for your current turn. This is one of the learning curves for ultra.", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T15:07:21.647000+00:00", "type": 19, "mentions": ["299711905751105536"], "reply_to": "1423686039267971153"}
{"id": "1423689235671552082", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "299711905751105536", "author_name": "pickles4701", "content": "I do enjoy putting a few swarm cards in there", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T15:12:44.651000+00:00"}
{"id": "1423689888812892285", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "299711905751105536", "author_name": "pickles4701", "content": "I don't really understand why quasar exists. Is it because some skills would be too op with leap?", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T15:15:20.372000+00:00"}
{"id": "1423690033344544839", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "299711905751105536", "author_name": "pickles4701", "content": "Leap is more fun", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T15:15:54.831000+00:00"}
{"id": "1423690250273951885", "channel_id": "1400749543288475770", "author_id": "693983290423509042", "author_name": "climbkaly", "content": "Exactly.\n\nClem providing 250 strength in ultra space can be abused.\n\nExample build up to turn 1 quasar, turn 2 ultra space and have 300 permanent strength before enemy turn", "timestamp": "2025-10-03T15:16:46.551000+00:00"}
